      "description_long": "Fegina Beach is the main beach of Monterosso and the only extensive sandy beach in the Cinque Terre. This beautiful stretch of coastline features both private lido sections with organized umbrellas and sunbeds, as well as free public beach areas. The beach is famous for its rows of colorful striped parasols (green and orange being particularly iconic) and is backed by hotels, restaurants, and cafes. In 2006, Forbes Traveler listed it among the 25 sexiest beaches in the world. The sand is mixed with pebbles, and the water is clear and suitable for swimming. Equipment rental is available for water sports.",
